air, a full beard, and a plaid shirt appears next. He bites into a pretzel-like snack on the left. On the right, a hand dips or lifts a small pretzel from the jar, coated in chocolate. The chocolate stretches downward in a glossy ribbon before tapering into a drip over the mouth of the jar.\n\nA blonde adult woman in a dark sleeveless top appears on the left, smiling with her mouth open as she brings a strawberry to her lips. On the right, a hand lifts a strawberry from the jar; the lower half is coated in thick chocolate, which trails down in a narrow drip. The woman then bites into the strawberry, her face tightening slightly in a satisfied tasting expression.\n\nA young adult man with short dark hair, light skin, and a dark jacket over a white shirt appears on the left. He holds a pale green celery stick and eats it. On the right, a hand spreads chocolate along another celery stick with a knife above the open jar. He chews, then smiles with a playful, pleased look while still holding the celery.\n\nThe imagery shifts to a close view of glossy, flowing chocolate. The word “HERSHEY’S” appears raised in dark letters within the chocolate surface, as if embossed or molded into it. The chocolate ripples and smooths over the letters until they disappear beneath the shiny surface.\n\nThe view then reveals the Hershey’s Spreads jar more closely, with the label filling the screen. Three jars are displayed together on a white surface: a larger chocolate jar in the center with the silver lid and “NEW!” label, flanked by two smaller jars in the background. The labels show different varieties, including chocolate and chocolate with almonds. The jars slide and reposition into a final lineup: three Hershey’s Spreads jars evenly spaced against the white background. The center jar is the largest and reads “chocolate with hazelnut” on an orange label; the smaller jar on the left reads “chocolate with almonds,” and the smaller jar on the right reads “chocolate.” Each jar has the same dark brown Hershey’s branding, a silver-gray lid, and images of chocolate with fruit on the label.",
